        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 4 at 2:01PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 201 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Escalante, moving east at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Escalante and Boulder.

This includes Utah Route 12 between mile markers 58 and 86.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
